frameDefinitions: An Item is in a state of dryness.
In this frame, an Agent or Cause changes the duration of an Event.
A Visitor arrives at the Host_location as a guest of the Host, for the purpose of achieving a Purpose.
A Figure is characterized as near the Ground, according to some contextually given scale.
An Evader moves under its own power to thereby avoid Capture  or contact with a Pursuer, also generally moving under its own power.
A State_of_affairs has held and continues to hold up to the Reference_occasion.
frameExamples: Don't let him <t>prolong</t> the discussion to an absurd length.
I'm gonna <t>drop</t> <t>in</t> on Kieth for a while.
She put her shoes <t>under</t> the table .
<t>To date</t>, the Department already has numerous requests for new systems to be developed.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
The sentient entity that changes the duration of the <fen>Event</fen>.
An event that causes the change in Event duration.
The time at which the change in duration of the Event is caused.
The <fen>Visitor</fen> arrives at the Host_location to visit the <fen>Host</fen> for a <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The <fen>Host</fen> is the person highly associated with the goal location of the <fen>Visitor</fen>, and who allows the <fen>Visitor</fen> onto his/her territory, and possibly to make use of available resources. The <fen>Host</fen> and <fen>Visitor</fen> and in a host-guest relationship.
The <fen>Host_location</fen> is a place primarily associated with the <fen>Host</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when arriving occurs.
The larger area within which the visiting takes place.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The <fen>Evader</fen> moves under its own power to <fen>Capture</fen> or contact with the <fen>Pursuer</fen>. Normally the <fen>Evader</fen> frame element is expressed as an external argument.
The <fen>Pursuer</fen> is going after the <fen>Evader</fen> unless they act.
An actual or hypothetical  event in which the <fen>Pursuer</fen> takes physical control of the <fen>Evader</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the Evading occurs.
A state which holds prior to and up through the <fen>Reference_occasion</fen>.
The time or event (normally speech time) with respect to which the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is located.

<fex>The cat</fex> is next to the mat.
